The paper deals with graph embeddings, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of book embeddings is closely related to graph drawing and graph theory, which are also relevant subfields of computer science. The paper also involves analyzing the structure of graphs, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of finding a book embedding with a constant number of pages can be seen as a graph theoretic problem, which is related to graph theory (cs.GT).
